            <section class="my-5">
              <h3 id="each-item">Nested each-[item]</h3><p>By nesting elements bound by <code>rv-each</code>, a scope is created for each nest level. The variables from parent scopes can be acessed by child ones, using a resolution algorithm similar to JavaScript prototype chain, i.e., looks for current scope if not found, look in parent scope repeating until find.</p>
<pre><code class="language-html">&lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;li rv-each-category=&quot;categories&quot;&gt;
    { category.name }
    &lt;ul&gt;
      &lt;li rv-each-todo=&quot;category.todos&quot;&gt;
        &lt;input
          type=&quot;checkbox&quot;
          rv-checked=&quot;todo.done&quot;
          rv-data-category-id=&quot;category.id&quot;&gt;
          { %category% } - { %todo% } - { todo.name }
      &lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;ul&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
</code></pre>
<!-- A more complex example can be found [here](https://codepen.io/blikblum/pen/MKXXOX?editors=1010#0) -->

